    <summary>Command-line client for Pangolin (meta package -> pangolin-cli.install)</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[Pangolin CLI is the official command-line client for Pangolin, an identity-aware, self-hostable tunneled reverse proxy and mesh VPN built on WireGuard. It works with both Pangolin Cloud and self-hosted Community/Enterprise servers.

This is a **meta package**: it installs the Pangolin CLI by taking a dependency on [pangolin-cli.install](https://community.chocolatey.org/packages/pangolin-cli.install). Install `pangolin-cli` if you prefer the plain package name; it always pulls the matching installer package.

### Features
- Authenticate to Pangolin Cloud or a self-hosted server (`pangolin login`)
- Apply configuration and blueprints as code (`pangolin apply`)
- List resources and show client status (`pangolin list`, `pangolin status`)
- Reach resources with identity-aware `pangolin ssh` and `pangolin scp`

### Compatibility and requirements
- Windows 10/11 (per upstream support)
- Administrator privileges may be required
- The VPN tunnel commands (`up`/`down`) are Linux-only; on Windows the tunnel is handled by the Pangolin GUI client
- For the tunnel-based commands (`ssh`/`scp`) on Windows, also install the Pangolin GUI client (`choco install pangolin`) — it provides the VPN tunnel the CLI connects through

### Disclaimer
This Chocolatey package is community-maintained and is not created, endorsed, or supported by Fossorial, Inc.

---

[choco://pangolin-cli](choco://pangolin-cli)

To use choco:// protocol URLs, install the (unofficial) package "choco-protocol-support".

---

**Note**: This package is automatically updated. If it is out of date by more than a day or two, please contact the maintainer(s).]]></description>
